The paper discusses a clustering method designed for the Hadoop distributed data platform, which suggests it falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also focuses on fuzzy clustering, which is a subfield of machine learning and data mining, indicating it could belong to the subcategories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of MapReduce programming model, which is commonly used in big data processing, suggesting it could belong to the subcategory of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed method, which is a common concern in the field of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
